<item>
            <title>[JDK-8293117] Add atomic bitset functions</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8293117</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>We need an Atomic version of setting bits, e.g. and/or/xor, like the one in accessFlags for general purpose use.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
From [~jrose]&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Suggestions for API shape:&lt;br/&gt;
Mimic whatever the intel intrinsics do for and/or/xor/add.  Prefer their names.&lt;br/&gt;
But, stay within the boundaries of what the C++ atomic API does (omit op-and-fetch, keep only fetch-and-op).  Use their names if it makes sense.&lt;br/&gt;
Key requirement: Have the return value contain enough information to infer the previous state of the variable, for those who care.&lt;br/&gt;
Key requirement: Robustly support &#8220;set one bit&#8221; and &#8220;clear one bit&#8221;, probably by logior and logand of multi-bit masks.&lt;br/&gt;
Higher-level bit setter could be update_bits(T bits, bool new_state) -&amp;gt; T old_bits.  The higher-level setter could use the optimization of not issuing a CAS if the bit (or bits) is (are) in the desired new state already.</description>
